    "body": "At some points described (https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/issues/326) spark will invalidate the output from an executor, and it may retry to run tasks there.\r\n\r\nWith the retry, now we have a store that has old/stale buffers that are never going to be read.\r\n\r\nThis just tracks figuring out how to hook into the invalidation (may need a change in Spark) so that we can remove the catalog data. Pending transfers for these blocks should be cancelled also as part of this.\r\n\r\n",
